User Input Validation
User Input validation mechanism is responsible of validate data before executing the business logic, avoiding to execute code if we know that inputs will not work.In the managed bean, you can decorate the properties of the java bean using standard annotations defined in the JSF 303 

@NotNull
@Min(value = 5)
@Max(value = 99)
private int age;
public int getAge() {
  return age;
}
In the JSP 

<h:inputText id="age" value="#{inputPanelManagedBean.age}">
<f:ajax execute="age" event="blur" render="age-error" />
</h:inputText>
<p:messages id="age-error" for="age" />
